    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-02-07T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-02-07T21:00:00-05:00" n="990"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d990">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.932/2–849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-08T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 8, 1949—10 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 9—12:29 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>338. [To Consul at Tihwa:<note n="8" xml:id="d990fn8">J. Hall Paxton.</note>]
                    Please keep Embassy and Department promptly informed visit of Chang Chih-chung
                    your area, including anticipated “exploratory talks” or actual negotiations with
                    Soviet representatives on commercial treaty between Sinkiang and USSR. (ReEmbtel
                    283 to Department February 1, repeated Consulate General Canton 16 and Tihwa
                    11.)</p>
                <p>Sent Tihwa 12; repeated Chungking 7, Department 338, Office Embassy Canton
                    24.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
